To the Kings Most Excellent Majesty. Dread Sovereign, having seen a proclamation wherein your Majesty complains of the injuries you receive in your customs, I could not withhold, but, as in duty bound, humbly present you with a few of those malignant roots from whence they spring, whereby navigation and trade are also much decayed ... Bower, Richard, fl. 1662. Charles II, King of England, 1630-1685.
1 sheet ([1] p.).
s.n., [London : 1661]
